@page "/"
<PageTitle>IdbBlazor Demo</PageTitle>

<h1>IdbBlazor – EF Core-style IndexedDB for Blazor</h1>

<p>
    This sample demonstrates a complete IndexedDB integration built with IdbBlazor.
    Navigate to the <a href="products">Products</a> or <a href="blog">Blog Posts</a>
    pages to see CRUD, full-text search, live queries, and versioned migrations in action.
</p>

<h2>Features demonstrated</h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>EF Core-style context &amp; DbSet</strong> — see <code>AppDb.cs</code></li>
    <li><strong>Data annotations</strong> — <code>[IdbKey]</code>, <code>[IdbIndex]</code>, <code>[IdbFullTextIndex]</code>, etc.</li>
    <li><strong>Fluent ModelBuilder</strong> — versioned schema with <code>UseVersion(1, ...)</code></li>
    <li><strong>LINQ queries</strong> — <code>Where</code>, <code>OrderBy</code>, <code>Take</code>, <code>Skip</code></li>
    <li><strong>Full-text search</strong> — <code>.Search("term")</code> via multi-entry shadow indexes</li>
    <li><strong>Transactions</strong> — <code>db.TransactionAsync(tx =&gt; ...)</code></li>
    <li><strong>Live queries</strong> — <code>.LiveQuery()</code> backed by polling</li>
    <li><strong>Versioned migrations</strong> — automatic schema upgrade + data migration callbacks</li>
</ul>
